ter Stallone, Meryl Streep, Sigourney Weaver, Bruce Willis, and the "Brat Pack"—stars in the drama of this decade. Acting for America focuses on the way these film icons have engaged in and defined some major issues of cultural and social concern to America during the 1980s. Scholars employing a variety of useful approaches explore how these movie stars' films speak to an increased audience awareness of advances in feminism, new ideas about masculinity, and the complex political atmosphere in the Age of Reagan. The essays demonstrate the range of these stars' contributions to such conversations in a variety of films, including blockbusters and major genres.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 0aMotion picture actors and actresseszUnited StatesvBiography. 7aPERFORMING ARTS / General.2bisacsh1 aBaker, Aaron, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBaker, Aaron.1 aBell-Metereau, Rebecca, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBell-Metereau, Rebecca.1 aBrown, William, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBrown, William.1 aDeAngelis, Michael, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDeAngelis, Michael.1 aEberwein, Robert, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEberwein, Robert, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aEberwein, Robert.1 aGabbard, Krin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGabbard, Krin.1 aHolmlund, Chris, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHolmlund, Chris.1 aKnee, Adam, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKnee, Adam.1 aLane, Christina, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLane, Christina.1 aMizejewski, 